00:49.410 --> 00:51.652
So yes, so today we're going to be speaking about wisdom.

00:52.653 --> 01:00.501
And as you know, if you've been in church over the last couple of weeks, you know that we have been going through a series called Unshakable.

01:01.361 --> 01:03.323
And this is the fourth talk in that series.

01:04.244 --> 01:11.171
And when I was preparing for today, I was thinking about the series that we're doing and why.

01:11.511 --> 01:14.734
Because there has to be a reason why we pick these topics.

01:15.315 --> 01:16.176
They're not arbitrary.

01:16.196 --> 01:18.578
They're not just for the sake of it.

01:19.106 --> 01:23.652
And we have had some pretty amazing series over the last couple of years if you've been in church.

01:24.172 --> 01:33.644
And I think this one in particular, we have to accept the fact that life isn't easy sometimes.

01:34.846 --> 01:41.394
And we all from time to time go through situations, challenges in life that

01:41.730 --> 01:42.712
try to shake us.

01:43.593 --> 01:45.015
That's just the reality of life.

01:45.897 --> 01:50.885
I don't think that there's anybody in this church today that hasn't been through something at some point.

01:51.667 --> 01:58.578
There may be many of us who are in this room now who are currently navigating something that's a bit difficult.

01:58.946 --> 02:02.592
And so that's the reality of living in a fallen world.

02:02.752 --> 02:06.699
You know, the Christian walk is not a casual stroll through the Metro.

02:06.960 --> 02:08.482
It's difficult at times.

02:09.724 --> 02:11.047
But it's not all bad news.

02:11.187 --> 02:12.789
It's some very, very good news.

02:12.910 --> 02:15.855
And that is that we are not left to do this walk alone.

02:16.636 --> 02:18.078
We have the word of God.

02:18.319 --> 02:19.481
We have the Father.

02:19.521 --> 02:22.546
And there is so much

02:22.850 --> 02:24.556
gold in the Word of God.

02:25.520 --> 02:30.258
It provides us with every single thing that we need to be able to navigate through life.

02:30.594 --> 03:00.580
Second Timothy 3, 16 says that all scripture is inspired by God and is useful and it's all useful and I think we can sometimes have a tendency to focus on the areas of the Bible that are a bit more familiar and a bit easier to navigate but actually the entirety of scripture is useful for our lives and what I enjoy about series like this is that it gives us the opportunity to go into parts of the Bible that we maybe don't actually spend that much time in because they're a bit strange and they're a bit complicated and

